# Accessibility and Responsive Rule

The redesigned auth pages must be beautiful and accessible.

## Accessibility Requirements

Mandatory:

- use semantic `form`;
- connect labels to inputs using `htmlFor` and `id`;
- keep visible labels, not placeholder-only fields;
- support keyboard navigation;
- support Enter to submit form;
- provide visible focus states;
- provide `aria-label` for icon-only buttons;
- password visibility button must have accessible label;
- validation errors must be associated with fields;
- error messages must be readable;
- disabled states must be clear;
- text contrast must be adequate on dark background.

## Keyboard Behavior

Check:

- Tab order is logical.
- Checkbox is keyboard accessible.
- Password visibility button is keyboard accessible.
- Submit button is reachable.
- Links are reachable.
- Focus is never hidden.

## Responsive Requirements

Desktop must match the references first.

Then test and adapt for:

- 1920×1080;
- 1440×900;
- 1366×768;
- 1280×720;
- tablet width;
- mobile width if supported.

## Mobile / Small Screen Rules

On smaller screens:

- reduce card padding;
- reduce brand size;
- reduce title size;
- keep input/button touch targets at least 44px high;
- avoid horizontal scrolling;
- keep footer links readable;
- preserve spacing hierarchy.

Example:

```css
@media (max-width: 720px) {
  .auth-card {
    width: calc(100% - 32px);
    padding: 36px 24px;
    border-radius: 22px;
  }

  .brand {
    font-size: 40px;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-size: 30px;
  }
}
```
